versions.bodyMarkdown:
# Features

The phone will no longer go to sleep when the SunPower Pro Connect app is used to commission devices.

# Bug Fixes

User is able to RETRY and continue navigation in the FIRMWARE UPDATE screen when the storage firmware update fails.

# Features
 - You can now view the Contract number and Finance type for the site in the CUSTOMER INFORMATION screen. 


 ![contract number and finance type on home screen](data:image/png;base64,) 
 - The text is now easier to read especially under the sun. We’ve increased the color contrast so you can easily read the messages and the errors in the App.

# Features
 - Users will now see the PVS5 grid profile downloaded in the FIRMWARE MANAGEMENT screen. We're working to add features for PVS5 support and will be rolling out additional features in the following weeks.

# Bug Fix
 - You will not be logged out in the middle of commissioning anymore.

# Bug fixes
 - The firmware update screen will no longer freeze and will allow you to proceed with commissioning without requiring you to restart the App.

# Features
 - You will now get a banner on the INSTALL tab if panel model type is missing for microinverters previously commissioned. This can happen when the site was previously commissioned with SunPower Console. When you see the banner make sure to tap on ASSIGN MODELS and follow the steps to set the panel model type. 


 ![missing models image](data:image/png;base64,)

 - You will now be notified in the ProConnect app if there are any issues impacting commissioning. A banner will be displayed on the home screen to provide you details about the issue and the expected resolution and also we will provide communication once the issue is resolved.

![issue notifications](data:image/png;base64,)
 # Bug Fixes 

 - Fixed issue with grid profiles sometimes not loading.

# Features
- We've added improvements to SunVault storage system check.
- On the CONFIGURE PVS NETWORK screen, you will now get a "No internet connection" status when you're connected to the homeowners WiFi or Ethernet but there is no internet connection.

![no internet connection](data:image/png;base64,)

# Bug Fixes
- The panel layout now displays the correct status  after successful commissioning with panels placed. 
- Removed the now unnecessary modal for notifying about errors during firmware downloads.
- The bug with the module model types not loading is now fixed.

# Improvements

We've made changes to the DEVICES screen after the discovery process so you can GO BACK and add or delete MIs if any errors were reported.

![devices screen with back button](data:image/png;base64,)
# Bugs fixes

The issue with overlapping sections that made it difficult to view and read MI SNs is now fixed.

![overlap error](data:image/png;base64,)

# Bug fixes

REPLACE PVS flow error where commissioning failed due to no payload is now addressed. You will now be able to replace and commission the new PVS.

# Improvements

MIs not communicating or disconnected will now report an “Error” in the status tab under Power Production.



![power production errors](data:image/jpeg;base64,)



The hamburger menu now has a Settings icon to help you view the PV checklist items before commissioning, and log out from the ProConnect App if needed.



![hamburger menu with settings](data:image/jpeg;base64,)



![settings page](data:image/jpeg;base64,)


# Bugs fixes

The new changes to the App will take you to the firmware management screen if an update is required and then continue with commissioning.

# CT setup and grid profile changes
Pro Connect now requires setting CT and grid profile configurations before you begin commissioning. This helps identify the CT configurations and display accurate production and consumption data in the Status tab.

![image of ct and grid profile](data:image/png;base64,) 
# Changes to Production CT requirement
Production CTs are required to complete commissioning of Equinox systems with this release. You will not be able to complete commissioning unless the production CTs are installed.
SunPower has released Live Data, a new feature for homeowners and installers that allows them to view real-time production and consumption data from their mySunPower and SunPower Pro Connect applications. However, in order to utilize this data, all systems are required to have a Production CT installed.
![Image of production ct error modal](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
# Required and Optional fields
We’ve made it easier to identify the required configurations before you can complete commissioning. The required fields are now marked with an asterisk (*).
![Image of asteriks on configs page](data:image/png;base64,)
# Bug fix for commissioning error
COMMISSIONCFG4005: Specified panelModel undefined at INVERTER/E00* is not in catalog –  If you run into this error at a site with MIs already commissioned, you’re able to ‘Edit panel models’ as shown below and set the model type in order to commission the site.
This functionality provides you a way to edit the panel model after commissioning.
![image of editing panel models](data:image/png;base64,)

# Bug Fix

Sites previously commissioned with Sunpower Console will no longer fail commissioning in Pro Connect due to missing panel data. User will have the option to select the panel model type before  commissioning.

# PVS WiFi connection improvements

Pro Connect will now display the PVS WiFi connection status. Look for the connection link icon on the top right corner in Pro Connect. During commissioning, if Pro Connect loses connection with the PVS you will see the icon turn red.

![Image of connection link icon](data:image/png;base64,)

![Image of connection pop up](data:image/png;base64,)

# Error reporting improvements

Error messages for Pro Connect have been improved. You can now see error messages displayed along with the error codes for commissioning failures.

# Bug fixes

Pro Connect now supports scanning MIs that start with serial number "20". The issue with grid profile sometimes not being displayed in the configuration screen has been fixed.

# Tab text change

"Live Status" tab name is now changed to "Status"

# Site address display
SunPower Pro Connect will now display the site address in all views in the App after a site is selected. It will be located at the top of each screen.

# Pre-commissioning checklist
With this feature, you will now be reminded of a list of required & suggested items for commissioning. It ensures that you don't forget any important items before you begin commissioning.

# Changes to commissioning successful screen
You will now see a message that "Commissioning was successfully completed" after submitting your configuration successfully. This will indicate to a user that commissioning was completed properly. Previously the screen displayed a message that stated that "Configuration was saved successfully".
